    <briefdescription>
<para>Describes the properties needed to create a GPU buffer. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem>
<para>debugName: This label can be applied as debug label for gpu debugging. </para>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<para>usage: Bits describing the intended usage and properties of the buffer. </para>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<para>byteSize: Length of buffer in bytes </para>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<para>vertexStride: The size of a vertex in a vertex buffer. This property is only required for vertex buffers. </para>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<para>initialData: CPU pointer to initialization data of buffer. The memory is consumed immediately during the creation of the <ref refid="class_hgi_buffer" kindref="compound">HgiBuffer</ref>. The application may alter or free this memory as soon as the constructor of the <ref refid="class_hgi_buffer" kindref="compound">HgiBuffer</ref> has returned. </para>
</listitem>
</itemizedlist>
</para>
